.TH RLESS 1 "May 2026" "rcat" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rless \- page through Markdown (and many other source/config files) in the terminal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rless
.RI [ OPTIONS "] [" FILE "...]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rless
is a Markdown- and source-aware pager built on the same renderer as
.BR rcat (1).
It reads each
.I FILE
(or standard input when none is given), renders it with ANSI styling,
Unicode box-drawing, OSC 8 hyperlinks, syntax highlighting, and inline
images via
.BR chafa ,
and then drives an interactive viewport so you can scroll and search.
.PP
By default,
.B rless
treats input as
.B CommonMark
Markdown with GFM extensions. When the filename does not look like
Markdown (or
.B \-\-lang
forces a different language), it falls back to the built-in syntax
highlighter that knows ~60 languages and configuration formats.
.PP
When standard output is not a terminal, or
.B \-\-no\-pager
is given,
.B rless
behaves like
.BR rcat (1)
and writes the rendered output without entering the pager. This makes it
safe to use in pipelines.
.SH KEY BINDINGS
While the pager is active, the following keys are recognised:
.TP
.BR j ", Down arrow"
Scroll down one line.
.TP
.BR k ", Up arrow"
Scroll up one line.
.TP
.BR Space ", " f ", PageDown"
Scroll down one page.
.TP
.BR b ", PageUp"
Scroll up one page.
.TP
.B d
Scroll down half a page.
.TP
.B u
Scroll up half a page.
.TP
.BR g ", Home"
Jump to the top of the buffer.
.TP
.BR G ", End"
Jump to the bottom of the buffer.
.TP
.B /
Search forward. Type the pattern at the prompt and press Enter; ESC
cancels. The match is ASCII case-insensitive and applied to the
ANSI-stripped visible text of each line.
.TP
.B ?
Search backward. Same prompt semantics as
.BR / .
.TP
.B n
Jump to the next match in the search direction.
.TP
.B N
Jump to the previous match in the search direction.
.TP
.BR h ", " H
Show in-pager help. Press any key to dismiss.
.TP
.BR q ", Q, Ctrl-C"
Quit the pager.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a short help message (translated when a matching locale catalog is
installed) and exit.
.TP
.BR \-c " " \fIN\fR ", " \-\-columns " " \fIN\fR
Wrap output to
.I N
columns. Defaults to the terminal width as reported by
.B /dev/tty
(via
.BR TIOCGWINSZ ),
or to 80 if no controlling terminal is available. Values below 10 are
rejected. When the terminal is resized, the buffer is automatically
re-wrapped to the new width.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-plain
Strip all styling: no SGR escapes, no Unicode box-drawing, no hyperlinks.
The pager UI is still drawn, but with a plain status bar.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Disable colour but keep other styling (Unicode bullets, headings, etc.).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-hyperlinks
Never emit OSC 8 hyperlinks, even when the terminal advertises support.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-images
Skip inline images even when image rendering was compiled in.
.TP
.B \-\-allow\-web
Download and render
.B http(s)
image URLs. Off by default. Requires
.B libcurl
at build time.
.TP
.B \-\-web\-timeout " " \fISEC\fR
Per-image fetch timeout for
.BR \-\-allow\-web ,
in seconds. Default 10.
.TP
.B \-\-image\-height " " \fIN\fR
Cap rendered image height to
.I N
terminal rows. Default 20.
.TP
.B \-\-ascii
Force ASCII-only output. No box-drawing characters, no bullet glyphs.
.TP
.B \-\-color " " \fIMODE\fR
Force the colour mode. One of
.BR auto ,
.BR none ,
.BR 16 ,
.B 256
or
.BR truecolor .
.B auto
defers to terminal autodetection (the default).
.TP
.B \-\-lang " " \fILANG\fR
Force the input language regardless of filename or extension. Use
.B md
or
.B markdown
to run the Markdown renderer explicitly.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-pager
Skip the pager and write the rendered output to standard output, even
when standard output is a terminal. Equivalent to using
.BR rcat (1)
with the same arguments.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
If set to any value, disables colour.
.TP
.B COLUMNS
Overrides the autodetected terminal width.
.TP
.BR LANG ", " LC_ALL ", " LC_CTYPE ", " LC_MESSAGES
Drive locale selection for translated messages and Unicode detection.
.TP
.B RCAT_LOCALEDIR
Override the directory
.B gettext
searches for compiled message catalogs
.RB ( rcat.mo ).
.TP
.BR TERM ", " COLORTERM ", " TERM_PROGRAM ", " SSH_TTY ", " SSH_CONNECTION
Used to detect colour depth, OSC 8 hyperlink support, and whether the
session is over SSH.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
One or more input files could not be read or could not be parsed, or the
controlling terminal could not be opened.
.TP
.B 2
Invalid command-line usage (unknown option, malformed value).
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Page through this manual's README:
.PP
.RS
.nf
rless README.md
.fi
.RE
.PP
Page through a source file with syntax highlighting:
.PP
.RS
.nf
rless src/rless.cpp
.fi
.RE
.PP
Page through stdin (e.g. a remote document):
.PP
.RS
.nf
curl -fsSL https://example.com/post.md | rless
.fi
.RE
.PP
Behave like
.BR rcat (1)
\(em render and exit without entering the pager:
.PP
.RS
.nf
rless --no-pager README.md
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I @CMAKE_INSTALL_FULL_LOCALEDIR@/<lang>/LC_MESSAGES/rcat.mo
Compiled message catalogs.
.B rless
shares the
.B rcat
catalog.
.SH BUGS
Report issues at the project's tracker.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rcat (1),
.BR less (1),
.BR more (1),
.BR md4c (3),
.BR chafa (1),
.BR locale (1).
